{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9e7297f8-49a5-4f67-b27a-7993a2a46748","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"93b0d3b0-ed07-44d4-8d3f-459060c6f037","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the dotnet CLI - I can answer directly without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"67CA:2B537A:2AEF505:2F8746F:69FD3D55"},"id":"4bb30910-bd2c-46c0-856c-207f22d69974","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:33:15.355Z","parentId":"d27377c7-361a-4dbd-ba81-402f0fede830"}
